<section class="bridge">
  <div class="section-label reveal">The Catalog Bridge</div>
  <h2 class="section-heading center reveal reveal-heading" style="--reveal-delay: 80ms">Bring your whole library with you.</h2>
  <p class="section-body reveal" style="margin: 0 auto; --reveal-delay: 160ms">
    Coming from Lightroom or Capture One, or anything that writes XMP sidecars,
    like darktable or Bridge? Latent reads your ratings, color labels, keywords,
    titles, captions, and the places they were made, and carries them in. It only
    fills what's empty, so nothing you've already done in Latent gets touched.
  </p>
  <p class="bridge-coda reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 240ms">
    The one thing it leaves behind is the other app's develop settings. There's no
    honest way to translate another engine's edits, so Latent doesn't pretend to.
    Your stars and your words come over, your photographs start fresh.
  </p>
</section>
